{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10653", "repo": "rails", "body": "Sorry, my example was not really good.\r\n\r\nI was thinking on methods like form_for that need to pass arguments (like the form builder) that are not available in the context. This will allow us to make something like:\r\n\r\n~~~ ruby\r\ndef form_for args, &block\r\n  builder = Builder.setup args\r\n  content_tab :form, arguments: builder, &block\r\nend\r\n~~~\r\n\r\nCurrently, the form_for helper capture the block inside the same method and do not use the content_tag helper.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dccdbd3543c151008a36"}, "issue_id": 10653, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/18031752", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10653#issuecomment-18031752", "updated_at": "2013-05-16T21:57:02Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp", "login": "eloyesp", "gravatar_id": "224f5b1b5ee448ec8152236ede91908c", "html_url": "https://github.com/eloyesp", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/224f5b1b5ee448ec8152236ede91908c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F31e5166d0480706c0ea9f43ccecfb30c.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 173797, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eloyesp/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-05-16T21:57:02Z", "id": 18031752, "owner": "rails"}
